<p><b>Paul Virilio</b> (born 1932 in <a href="/wiki/Paris" title="Paris">Paris</a>, <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a>) is a <a href="/wiki/Culture_theory" title="Culture theory">cultural theorist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Urban_planning" title="Urban planning">urbanist</a>. He is best known for his writings about <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technology</a> as it has developed in relation to speed and power, with diverse references to architecture, the arts, the city and the military.</p>
